gon loot possible.  Any guesses how long it will take for the Cloak drop to be nerfed?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Walbort</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Could you post stats on the gloves and belt for the walkthrough? Screenshots would be even better.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Walbort Wholeheart<BR>Bristlebane Server</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I would, but i personally never saw them. They were ok, not uberly great, but alright.  All no drop, lore pieces.  If i see my mage buddies that won the things ill ask them to send me a SS.<P>I am thinking the cloak of flames drop is RARE.  i mean.. we killed him 4 times. other people have killed him on other servers a few times. and this is the only one we've seen... i think we were just lucky.<P>Although, the monks really like the stats of that mantle, so ask your local monkie to come help!  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Lora<P>------------------<BR>Loralienn CoeurTendre<BR>Xegony<BR>~Immortal~</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lemieux</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I was the monk who had the privledge of pulling Ixiblat (dang that thing is huge.. the mages with us were drooling!) to the Skyfire zone.<P>He spawns at neg 2000, pos 1300 when the shell is turned in (make sure the puller isn't standing too close to that loc heh). When agro'd he will still follow even if you get a fair distance ahead, unlike normal Kunark mobs, and he doesn't cause mobs he passes by to agro.<P>Any class could pull it honestly. Just make sure to use something with some range.. and don't let him get in melee range. The only real trick is trying not to agro other mobs as you run north to Skyfire.<P>Good luck clerics!<BR>Lemieux<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for coming to post Lem  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>*hugs* (and for pulling!)<P>Lora</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks for coming to post Lem  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>*hugs* (and for pulling!)<P>Lora<P>------------------<BR>Loralienn CoeurTendre<BR>Xegony<BR>~Immortal~</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sulfer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn,<P>Could give us the average lvl and composition of your team for taking Ixiblat, I am trying to determine if my guild can take him down or not (most ppl around 54).<P>Thank you,<P>S.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sure thing. we had 5 groups, but they were not all full.<P>I had 2 fully tank groups.  With monks/palis/warriors/etc.  Each of these groups had 2 clerics. One of them had a bard. (so 2 clerics a bard and 3 tanks, or 2 clerics and 4 tanks)  then i had another group with a cleric, couple tanks, and some utilities like chanter/shaman.<P>Then i had 2 groups, each with a cleric, and full of casters/chanter/necro/mage/wizzy and druid/shamans.<P>These people all ranged from 50-60, and i would say the mean was around 53.  <P><BR>This was pretty much overkill. <P>Total i had 3 chanters (one kept on naxot the WHOLE TIME we were there keeping him mezed/rooted/charmed to keep him out of the fight, and 2 had charmed wurms) 2 shamans, a TON of monks (thanks monkies!), couple rogues(put them in the tank groups, they will need healing from the aoe too), a bard, a handful of other tanks/hybrid types, a couple druids, 2 necros (i think) 4 or 5 mages and a few wizzyes thrown in there too. Of course, since we did 4 fights in a couple hours, few of these people left and a few others joined, and etc.<P>I would say this could be done with 4 groups of -55 people, or 3 groups of majority +55. and this is pretty easily with very little death.<P>One reason we had so many is so the downtime was minimal between fights, as we wanted to get 4 done as fast as possible.<P>I think thats about it  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><BR>any more questions?<P>Lora</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sulfer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thanks Lora,<P>Since I'm planning everything on this hunt I want to have it go smoothely, and calm down ppl who apprehend fighting an unknown lvl 60+.<P>S.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Vervain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Those that have pulled him, could he be aggroed and then have the puller "reeled" in via Call of The Hero so that the possibility of aggro on other creatures is diminished?  Or is it "not too far ahead, but farther than most Kunark critters"?<P>-V<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sulfer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn,<P>I just reread your post and noticed you mentionned that you kept an enc on Naxot duty at all times. Does that mean Naxot agroes Ixiblat (or Ixiblat agroes Naxot?). I am assuming you wanted to keep him alive just for doing quest several times in a row, but this is not necessary for a one time Ixiblat kill?<P>Thanks again,<P>S.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Oberan Lifebringer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">From what i hear Naxot immediately starts running straight to Xiblat and suicides when he gets there (probably from Xiblat killing him). If that happens i suppose you have to wait 3 hours for him to respawn (most groups dont have that kind of patience inbetween kills)<P>Oberan Lifebringer<BR>54th Vicar of Innoruuk<BR>Gankos Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Endar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">aye, had an enchanter on duty keeping naxot mezzed/charmed (for handing in items) at skyfire zoneline...  <P>Naxot is only needed to spawn ixiblat, after that you don't need him  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif">, so if you only have to kill ixiblat once, sure let him die  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/wink.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Loralienn</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Call of hero clears agro most the time so.. no. but anyone with sow can keep ahead of him (hes kinda slow) just make sure to stay out of aoe range and pull with a ranged weapon, and you will be fine.<P>What endar said, about naxot  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> (ie, yes, if you are killing him only once, you need not bother with naxot at all after turning in your shell, if you want to do 2 or more, you need to keep him busy mezed/rooted/charmed so that he does not try to kill ixiblat himself, and perish.)<P><BR>Anything else?  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Lora</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
